reviewText: Boring for me. Others might like it, but I did not. The picture is not sharp, but the sound is good. I did not even watch the whole movie I was so bored.

Ray Milland is always great in flicks, even if they aren't that good.  Here he plays a Yegg, Box man, or "Safecracker".  He gets suckered into a job by Barry Jones as a two-bit crook.

I noticed Jackie Collins as a secretary, and Ferdy Mayne (Conan the Destroyer (1984), Our Man in Havana (1959) in here as well.

94 min.
